# Comments: avoid adding them

When changing or adding code in this project:

- **Do not** add `//` or `/* */` comments that restate what the code does, section banners, or “obvious” explanations.
- **Do not** add `///` or `//!` doc comments on private helpers or on public items when the name and types already make the contract obvious.
- **Prefer** renaming, extracting functions, or tightening types so intent is clear without comments.

**Exceptions (only when truly needed):**

- License or required legal/header blocks already mandated by the project.
- A short comment is justified when it documents **non-obvious rationale** (e.g. a workaround, invariant, or safety contract) that cannot be expressed in the type system or API.

```rust
// ❌ BAD: comment duplicates the code
// Increment the counter
counter += 1;

// ✅ GOOD: no comment; name carries intent
pending_retries = pending_retries.saturating_sub(1);
```

Do not delete existing comments unrelated to your edit unless the user asks you to clean them up.
